                <ul>
                    <li>Price range: <span class="font-weight-700">₹6.20 L to ₹12.33 L</span> ex-showroom across petrol, AMT, and CNG trims</li>
                    <li>Positioned for young buyers who want SUV flair with modern convenience</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Powertrain & Performance</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Punch</h3>
               
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.2L Revotron</span> (3-cylinder) petrol: ~86 PS / 114 Nm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">5MT / optional AMT</span></li>
                    <li>CNG and EV variants available, but core comparisons focus on petrol</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Exter</h3>
               
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.2L Kappa II</span> petrol: 82 PS / 114 Nm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">5MT or 5-speed AMT</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Bi-fuel CNG variant</span> with 68 PS / 95 Nm (CNG)</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Fuel Economy (ARAI):</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Punch petrol: Not officially published; expected ~18 kmpl</li>
                    <li>Punch CNG/EV: N/A for 2025 petrol model</li>
                    <li>Exter petrol: <span class="font-weight-700">19.2 kmpl</span>, AMT ~19.2 kmpl</li>
                    <li>Exter CNG: <span class="font-weight-700">27.1 km/kg</span></li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Dimensions & Practical Usability</h2>
